# Tool Blessing Ritual

### A purification of objects for ritual use and their transformation into magical items.

(*The area is prepared by placing a quantity of each element in the
proper quarter, as well as preparing the altar in the usual way. If
available, a cauldron (empty) is placed in the center of the circle.
Candles are placed at each of the four corners and lit, progressing
deosil from the east. Salt and water are blessed, and the celebrants are
purified with them. A magic circle is cast, and watchtowers summoned.
The god is then drawn down as follows:  
The priest stands before the alter in the Osiris position, arms crossed
across chest and feet together. The Priestess kneels before him with
face and arms upraised.*)

