<td width="40"><strong>P:</strong></td>
<td>Spirits of the west, in water born<br />
In cool waters cleanse these tools<br />
And wash from them all hurt and harm<br />
This I ask, this charge I lay,<br />
By oak and ash and bitter thorn.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

(*The objects are moved by the priestess to the south quarter and moved
above the flames there.*)

