<td>Spirits of the south, in fire born<br />
In shining flames purify these tools<br />
And burn from them all impurities<br />
This I ask, this charge I lay,<br />
By oak and ash and bitter thorn.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

(*The objects are moved to the east quarter by the priest and moved
through the incense smoke.*)

