Make them flourish like grapes on the vine<br />
Spirits of earth, hearken unto me,<br />
As I do will, so more it be.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

(*The priest takes the tools from the altar and steps backwards. The
priestess stands at the altar facing south towards the priest. The
priest extends his right arm in parallel to the ground, between he and
the priestess, with the tools in his hand.*)

